From b58c12dab19acd7d83c44c0f3ae1c4ad6b2a5e91 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 22:25:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] airoha: an7563: bump CONFIG_SYS_BOOTM_LEN for the lzma kernel

After enabling CONFIG_LZMA, bootm now reaches the LZMA branch in
boot/image.c::image_decomp() but bails out with

    Image too large: increase CONFIG_SYS_BOOTM_LEN
    Must RESET board to recover

`unc_len` passed to lzmaBuffToBuffDecompress() defaults to
CONFIG_SYS_BOOTM_LEN. Upstream Kconfig falls back to 0x800000
(8 MiB) on 32-bit ARM (the 0x8000000 bucket is gated on
PPC || ARM64 || RISCV). Our OpenWrt 6.12 FIT kernels for AN7563
ship a 3.3 MiB lzma blob that expands to roughly 12-16 MiB, so
the 8 MiB cap rejects them.

Bump it to 0x2000000 (32 MiB), matching other OpenWrt-family
vendors with comparable ARMv7 kernels (i.MX8MP-icore,
stm32mp1-icore, ...). 32 MiB is well below the gap between
${loadaddr} (0x81800000) and the BL33 base (0x81E00000), and the
decompression destination 0x80088000 (just above the ATF reserve
at 0x80000000-0x80040000) has roughly 23 MiB of headroom up to
the FIT staging area at 0x81800000 before any physical overlap
matters. Real kernels stay around 12-16 MiB so headroom is
plentiful in practice.

Signed-off-by: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
---
 configs/an7563_evb_defconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig b/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
index a47c7503..b58c12da 100644
--- a/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
+++ b/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
@@ -15,6 +15,7 @@ CONFIG_BUILD_TARGET="u-boot.bin"
 CONFIG_FIT=y
 CONFIG_FIT_VERBOSE=y
 CONFIG_LZMA=y
+CONFIG_SYS_BOOTM_LEN=0x2000000
 CONFIG_BOOTDELAY=3
 CONFIG_DEFAULT_FDT_FILE="an7563-evb"
 CONFIG_SYS_PBSIZE=1049
-- 
2.43.0
